==English==

===Noun===
'''assault weapon''' (US term)
# A semi-automatic firearm similar in name, appearance, or design to a fully automatic firearm or military weapon.
# A firearm that meets a set of conditions designated by law.
# Any weapon employed in combat.

===Usage Note===
This term is considered to be pejorative by some. It is used primarily in a political context, and is rarely ascribed to weapons of military interest.